caption: Extremely pleasant staff. Helped us find seating for 6 while being mindful of Covid laws and restrictions. Fantastic place. Great food also!

Really good place in the south loop for coffee and catch up. Nice selection of breakfast sandwiches, coffees, cappuccinos, and tea lattes. Their sandwiches come with yummy chips. Fresh and tasty, and so are the chips. Cappuccino comes in an authentic cup. They also serve Impossible breakfast sausages.

Since we wanted to spend time here, we came here for coffee last week. We enjoy chit-chatting over a coffee cup. We picked this spot because one of the best places to get coffee is here. I just think chocolate overwhelms coffee, so you may think you're drinking hot chocolate. A try is worth it!
It's much more than a drinking place for coffee, and here I still experience a very relaxed period. I'll end up here several times just because I want to run from the office.
A well-planned menu to fit everyone's taste. If you want a nice cup of coffee and something to eat, I suggest this place. Best coffee, best service.
Cute little coffee shop that's also a great place to buy coffee beans.

We stopped here for lunch and were able to get a table without a wait and no reservation.  The chicken sandwich was amazing, but service was average.  We had a difficult time getting water refilled and getting the bill at the end, but I wouldn't hesitate to come back for the food!
Surely, I'll drop by here again! I'm so glad that I was finally able to find this place just in time for some strong coffee. Truly amazing! Thank you so much, guys!
This place is absolutely one of my favorites. I look forward to going back again. It has a cool interior.
Perfect place to catch up with friends
I was really pleased and happy. I love sandwiches and vegetarian pasta. It's a nice spot, actually. This I would recommend to others. We're here to have lunch.
They have great coffee and great sandwiches with bagels, and the service is very simple. Maybe he'll come back soon.

Their bagels were fresh & warm. Cream cheese also freshly made. They provided a side of house made chips for our longer wait time (which wasn’t too long). Chips were delicious!! Great food - would come again!  The team was also very friendly.

Absolutely love this place! Excellent service and delicious cakes. Super cute décor, too. I have a little rewards card where you get punches each time you make a purchase and it adds up pretty quickly , I recommend Cafe Press Chicago
very tasty. it has an awesome atmosphere. food is like a place in baltimore i loved.
Service is always excellent even when they have a full house. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. The bill was fair for the quality of food.
i give this place double thumbs up. looking forward to returning with my coworkers. prices were average for the menu.

Honestly i used to love this place. I live in the building above and used to bring all my friends here and visitors to get a nice latte. After COVID the quality has gone SO downhill. I don’t know about the food- i typically only order lattes, but the last 4 times i was here, I’ve had to throw my lattes out because they were THAT bad. I don’t want to go to Starbucks- i want to support local... but it’s embarrassing to bring friends here and have them throw out their drinks because they taste disgusting!!! Please train your staff to make good quality drinks.  Beware of getting lattes- they seem to be a hit or miss.
visited sat afternoon. the staff was very helpful and observant. prices were average for the menu.

I’ve lived down the street from Cafe Press for months and it’s my favorite coffee shop in the South Loop! I would say prices are similar to Starbucks, but the quality of their products are amazing! A pastry and medium iced latte was around $11 but you get what you pay for and won’t be disappointed! I can’t wait until my next visit!
it was so tasty.
Very filling.
quick and friendly service. this place has a nice feel to it.
super appetizing. the service was sociable and attentive. the bill was fair for the quality of food. feels like a place in los angeles i loved.
Visited at eight, it was not full. I look forward to going back again. Menu is similar to a restaurant in El Paso I loved.
Entered near ten, it was not crowded. Service is consistently great.
Egg sandwiches are very underwhelming. The yolk is dry and does not go well with the consistency of a breakfast sandwich. Coffee was sour.
Nice place to relax, people watch, eat good, etc.  The staff was very sociable and kind. It has a good feel to it.
I often meet people here to talk. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. It has a cool atmosphere.
Asked for a cappuccino, the “barista” basically handed me half a liter of boiled milk in a coffee cup, learn how to make coffee!! you are a coffee shop.
Good spot! Pre-pandemic it was a chill place to get some work done. Staff is friendly and they sell their own roasted coffee beans.

The lattes are tremendous and flavorful. The scones are delicious. The breakfast sandwiches are balanced and the coffee is quite good. This is a cafe and the ambiance suits it as such. It's a benefit to live close, because great coffee is a special thing.
Cafe Press is a great place to go! They serve soups, sandwiches, & lots of delicious drinks and food items! I went there with my daughter& friend since they highly recommended it!!!

Friendly staff and great coffee and tea selection. For coffee note that their size small is REALLY small. It's good, but overpriced. I also liked the lavender latte--usually I go for plain coffee but I tried it on a whim and it was unique and really good. For breakfast, they have decent egg sandwiches. You can customize if you want meat, cheese and what kind of bread (croissant, english muffin, bagel). A couple of times my english muffin has been kind of gummy, like it was microwaved? But generally they're quite good.

Our server was excellent, the room was clean and comfortable. My only complaint was that my coffee was warm rather than hot despite her remaking it, and my friends chai latte was rather bland. Overall the pastry was good, and I'm sure it was just the luck of the draw. I'll try it again next time.
Incredible local coffee shop with unique offerings and cozy atmosphere.

I like this coffee shop although don’t always habe certain croissants. I asked for almond and they gave me chocolate once. Depends on barista, some are nice and others (like the wrong croissant giver) doesn’t know what she was thinking. Coffee isngood however and. Ice place to do work. I do recommend however.
A small little cafe that offers creative coffee drinks and a variety of food! I loved the panini and macarons available. I want to go back to try their special - a lavender latte ☺️
Best coffee and croissant in Chicago!!!
Coffee and tea was excellent. No gluten free items though.

I've stopped by here a few times for coffee and breakfast, and really like the space. It's quiet, cozy, and has plenty of outlets should you need it. It's usually not too busy which I find pretty nice for getting work done.  The coffee and pastries are pretty standard. Once when I was there, they had a French toast muffin that they were testing out. It was incredible. It's basically what it sounds like--French toast in the shape of a muffin, and came with a small tub of maple syrup too. I'd recommend it if they still have it around! I've also had their smoothies and think it's not worth the price.
GREAT!!!!
A preferred evening place. Service is consistently above par. It has a cool feel to it. Atmosphere is similar to a place in Columbus I loved.

If you are looking for a coffee shop with amazing coffee and pastries, I highly recommend Cafe Press in Printers Row. Tucked away next door to Sociale, Cafe Press offers long communal tables, free wifi, and a great place to get some work done. I had their chai tea latte and butter croissant while working through my morning email. The staff were friendly, the portion size was great, and prices very reasonable. The coffeeshop is also on Ritual.co, which allows you to order ahead or order from your phone in store and skip the line.
I drank The Best Latte ever, not super hot no cold... the Girl was super friendly... and Cute! I will visit it more often. BTW looks like a great place to work, cozy and quiet! Love it.

I ordered from them using Caviar. They canceled more than half of my order without notification and sent no utensils. My food was cold. I paid an UNGODLY amount for an inedible sandwich and soggy fruit cup.

I like this coffee shop although don’t always habe certain croissants. I asked for almond and they gave me chocolate once. Depends on barista, some are nice and others (like the wrong croissant giver) doesn’t know what she was thinking. Coffee isngood however and. Ice place to do work. I do recommend however.
It's good

Good atmosphere, coffee and service. The have gluten free options for bakery and it’s always been fresh when I had it. I like the old newspapers on the walls and the way the seating is arranged. On weekends they can add a little “kick” to your drinks if you’re staying in. I like coming here.

Cafe is very cute with great tables and sitting areas. Barista with dark hair, usually works weekends is over the top rude and condescending to the point of eye rolling and hateful glares because you simply ordered a coffee, think "how dare you" attitude. Acts as if she has a high sense of ownership of the cafe. Food is very-very strange, tasteless, weird. No concept of spice or flavor. I tried a few items that were not edible, nothing is balanced with too much of one ingredient to a comical level, as if someone created it as a joke or a toddler created it with no rhyme or reason. Big and sloppy. Providing review now as I was planning to go to a cafe this morning and thinking how much I love the tables and design, the style reminds me of cafes when i lived in Montreal, but, it's just not worth rudeness and the odd tasteless food. I used to go after eating somewhere else and just have the coffee. The need a consultant with culinary training to go in as a secret shopper to provide feedback, clearly the owner has poor taste in food and there is a disconnect with the general population, especially south loop that has choice and generally average to above average palette at the least.
Straight forward coffee shop. Decent coffee and simple but good food.
I DO NOT RECOMMEND BUYING COFFEE. NOTHING MORE AND LESS.

I wish that I could give negative starts if I could. The waitress is so rude and mean. She has attitude towards the most of customers... coffee tastes like watery too. Don't go here unless you are looking for a place to study. The atmosphere is not too bad to study but just never expect anything more than that.. I wouldn't go back.
Good coffee and lunch spot (much needed in the neighborhood) but got a panini and it was cold in the center. Must have been an off day, will try again.

The cashier/waitress (didn't get her name, she was a black lady and looked to be in her mid 40's) was really, really rude. I sincerely cannot believe she is working front of house. If reviews were based on food alone I'd give this place four stars, because the food wasn't bad. But the staff left such a bad impression that I'll never go back. What a shame.

I'd eaten breakfast here a few times. The food is wonderfully prepared and to order. The atmosphere and service is nothing fancy but pleasant. I'd usually get work done on my laptop, as many others patrons do in the large windows or at a table. They offer free Wi-Fi. I also enjoy their music playlist. I've just tried a few items on their menu but I would trust everything to be pretty good.

Just don’t go here. The waitresses are mean and think it’s funny when you’re left waiting in an empty (completely empty) establishment for oatmeal. It took twenty minutes for my partners oatmeal to come out (my crappy egg sandwich came out within 5 minutes). Once we got the “oatmeal” it was awful. Literally it was more like soup (the oats were floating in sugar water) and it was half brown sugar. We each tasted it and gagged. I gave him a part of my sandwich so he could at least have something but since the sandwich wasn’t great either we just got up and left. Paid 15.00 for really bad service and inedible food. Just save your money and go literally anywhere else. Oh on the bright side now we both have upset stomachs from that weird egg sandwich.
Eli is great
Seems like a solid place and pretty sure they have some gluten-friendly eat items.

This is just another place run by formula in the Good Eats Group.A quick bite literally.I am a senior out for a nosh and a cup of joe in a relaxing environment near my home.Well for $2.45 in a cup that holds 4 sips,is was over the top expensive and average tasting at best.No better and smaller than the yellow arch’s coffee.This place is just another young people staring at their computer joint with no sense of community. Decor very interesting.All table and chairs.No comfortable living room style seating. Service Good.Parking non existent. AWARDED 1.5 YUMS ON A SCALE OF 3
Great neighborhood coffee shop. Be sure to get the reward punch card. It's free and you get a free drink after buying a dozen.
Strong coffee
